On the International Day for the Elimination of Violence Against Women, the US government reaffirms its commitment to ending gender-based violence. The article highlights the efforts made by the administration to address this issue, including the release of the National Plan to End Gender-Based Violence and the signing of an Executive Order to transform how the military handles sexual assault and domestic violence cases. The article emphasizes the disproportionate impact of gender-based violence on marginalized communities and the need to provide support and resources for survivors. The US government recognizes that the work is far from done and pledges to continue working towards a future where survivors are believed, offenders are held accountable, and violence against women and girls is no longer tolerated.